Key Match Events: Khama Billiat scored the winning penalty for Zimbabwe in the 34th minute
Kennedy Amutenya hit the woodwork with a close-range header from a corner
Marshal Munetsi missed a headed attempt following a corner
Prins Tjiueza hit the woodwork from a left-footed strike from the middle of the goal area
Post-Match Reflections: Zimbabwe secured all three points in matchday three of the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers
Namibia struggled to level matters despite increased activity on the ball
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zimbabwe held most of the ball during the first 10 minutes of the match but played the majority of the game inside their own half
The match was played at the Orlando Stadium
Others: Khama Billiat marked his return to South African soil on a successful note
Colin Benjamin's troops looked lively after the restart
